    <note>Xiong(1) Fang [15473] Nanchang FZ, 30.3b. See also documentation for great grandson-in-law, Huang(2) Ce [15472]. The Xiong(1) were an important Nanchang lineage from Tang, with jinshi recorded for Nanchang, Jinxian and Fengcheng counties from the Tang Kaiyuan period through the Song and into Ming. I have only included those Xiong(1) with documented kinship ties to Fang. CHECK Nanchang FZ for a possible reconstruction of the whole lineage. A Poyang branch of the Xiong(1) seems to have established itself first as a degree-holding family, followed by Xiong(1) in Nanchang, Chunren, etc., as one would predict.</note>
